29:   `BondInsufficient` (SG-N1-A4.1).
30:2. **Step 2.5 — bond bounded by balance**: `bond > verifier_balance`
31:   rejects with `VerifyBondOutOfBounds` (SG-N1-A4.2).
32:3. **Step 3 — target liveness**: target_work_tx ∈ `stakes_t` else
33:   `VerifyTargetNotAccepted` (SG-N1-A4.3).
34:4. **Step 3.5 — duplicate gate**: `(verifier, target) ∈
35:   agent_verifications_t` rejects with `VerifyDuplicate` (SG-N1-A4.4).
36:5. **Step 4 — solvency defense-in-depth**: structurally unreachable
37:   post-Step-2.5; preserved.
38:6. **Step 5 — atomic transfer**: `balances_t[verifier] -= bond`;
39:   `stakes_t[verify.tx_id] = StakeEntry { amount: bond, staker: verifier,
40:   task_id }`.
41:7. **Step 5b — duplicate-set insert**: `(verifier, target) →
42:   agent_verifications_t` (SG-N1-A4.5 positive control).
43:8. **Step 6 — monetary invariants**: `assert_no_post_init_mint` +
44:   `assert_total_ctf_conserved` + `assert_claim_amount_backed_by_escrow`.
45:9. **OMEGA-Confirm path**: on `verdict == Confirm` AND target's task has
46:   `task_markets_t` entry, create `ClaimEntry { claimant:
47:   target_stake.staker, amount: total_escrow, ... }` for the **proposer**
48:   (NOT the verifier).
49:
50:## §2 What the existing VerifyTx arm DOES NOT do
51:
52:### §2.1 Gap-A — verifier reputation accumulation
53:
54:`src/state/sequencer.rs` VerifyTx arm does NOT touch
55:`q.economic_state_t.reputations_t`. A grep of `src/state/sequencer.rs`
56:for `reputations_t` returns ONLY a forward-pointing doc-comment at line
57:3857 ("SlashTx / SettlementTx / ProvisionalAcceptTx /
58:ReputationUpdateTx"). No code mutates `reputations_t` in any arm — only
59:`Default::default()` (== `Reputation(0)`) per agent.
60:
61:Per `CROSS_PROBLEM_PERSISTENCE_REPORT.md` §3 row 3 "No `reputations_t`
62:entries accumulated (no `VerifyTx` cycle yet; reputation += score only
63:on accepted Verify per TB-N1 A4. **G2P module pending**)".
64:
65:The persistence-report wording "per TB-N1 A4" is aspirational — the
66:actual TB-N1 A4 charter does NOT scope reputation accumulation. A5
67:(Class-2, separately scoped: "prompt economic feedback — recent
68:FinalizeRewardTx + rejection penalty") is the forward atom.
69:
70:### §2.2 Gap-B — bond return at run-resolve
71:
72:`balances_t[verifier] -= bond` at admission is final until something
73:explicitly credits the bond back. No code path returns the bond:
74:- No FinalizeRewardTx arm credits the verifier's bond back into
75:  `balances_t`.
76:- No TerminalSummaryTx / TaskExpireTx / TaskBankruptcyTx unlocks the
77:  `stakes_t[verify.tx_id]` entry.
78:- `stakes_t[verify.tx_id]` persists across the full run; on next-run
79:  resume the entry remains visible (G1.1 SG-G1.3 balances reconstruction
80:  preserves this).
81:
82:Net effect today: every accepted VerifyTx is a **permanent debit** of
83:`bond_micro` from the verifier's balance. There is no positive economic
84:incentive for the verifier — the OMEGA-Confirm claim flows to the
85:proposer, not the verifier.
86:
87:## §3 Why this is Class-1 OBS, not a Class-3+ fix attempt
88:
89:G2P module is Class 2 per charter §1 Module G2P "Class peak: 2" with
90:"§8 packet required: no". A reputation-credit or bond-return fix would
91:require:
92:- Sequencer admission arm code modification → Class 3 minimum
93:- Potential VerifyTx schema extension (per-verdict reward shape) →
94:  Class 4 STEP_B
95:- Architect §8 packet
96:- Per-atom dual audit timing
97:
98:Per `feedback_no_workarounds_strict_constitution`: silently coding the
99:fix under a Class-2 atom would violate the no-shortcut user directive.
100:The correct forward path is:
101:1. **G2P.3 OBS** (this file) — make the gap visible.
102:2. **G3.1 / G3.2** (charter §1 Module G3; Class 3 / 4): persistent PnL +
103:   solvency + AutopsyCapsule emission. G3.2 is the Class-4 §8 packet
104:   boundary that gates Verify reward/bond-return as part of a coherent
105:   PnL contract.
106:3. Optionally TB-N1 A5 (Class-2 forward; "prompt economic feedback —
107:   recent FinalizeRewardTx + rejection penalty") if the architect rules
108:   it independent of G3.
109:
110:## §4 Forward closure criteria
111:
112:This OBS closes when EITHER:
113:- A Class-3+ atom lands sequencer-side reputation accumulation (e.g.,
114:  `reputations_t[verifier] += 1` on accepted VerifyTx) AND bond-return
115:  semantics on run-resolve, with its own ship-gate test; OR
116:- An architect §10 reclassification confirms the current
117:  "permanent-debit verify" semantics as canonical (zero reward — verify
118:  is altruistic protocol-maintenance only), in which case this OBS is
119:  retired with a verbatim quote.
120:
121:Neither path is in scope for TB-G G2P.* — they are forward Class-3+
122:work.
123:
124:## §5 Binding test pins current contract
125:
126:`tests/constitution_g2p_verify_reward_bond_return.rs` SG-G2P.6 binds the
127:CURRENT contract so any future fix is gate-time-caught:
128:- SG-G2P.6.a: this OBS file exists at the expected path with the
129:  expected forward-closure section.
130:- SG-G2P.6.b: TB-N1 A4 admission contract present in
131:  `src/state/sequencer.rs` (bond debit + stakes_t insert +
132:  agent_verifications_t insert source-grep).
133:- SG-G2P.6.c: current code DOES NOT mutate `reputations_t` from any
134:  sequencer arm (negative-witness source-grep). Any future commit that
135:  adds `reputations_t.*insert` to sequencer.rs flips this assertion and
136:  surfaces the gap-closure work for review.
137:
138:## §6 Cross-references
139:
140:- TB-G charter §1 Module G2P atom G2P.3:
141:  `handover/tracer_bullets/TB_G_GENERATIVE_ARENA_charter_2026-05-11.md`
142:- G1.2-7 R2 persistence report:
143:  `handover/evidence/g_phase_g1_2_full_2026-05-11T23-36-38Z/CROSS_PROBLEM_PERSISTENCE_REPORT.md`
144:- TB-N1 A4 charter (no reputation/bond-return scope):
145:  `handover/tracer_bullets/TB_N1_AGENT_ECONOMY_PHASE_2_charter_2026-05-10.md`
146:- TB-N1 A4 admission test (TB-N1 A4 gates GREEN witness):
147:  `tests/constitution_n1_agent_economy_a4.rs`
148:- Forward Class-3+ atom row: TB-G charter §1 Module G3 (G3.1 / G3.2).

